{{模板:Global surveillance}}
全球監控（Global surveillance）是一種針對全體人口的跨國[[大規模監控|大規模監控]]<ref>{{cite book|language = en|last=Webb|first=Maureen|title=Illusions of Security: Global Surveillance and Democracy in the Post-9/11 World|url = https://archive.org/details/illusionsofsecur0000webb|year=2007|publisher=[[城市之光書店|城市之光書店]]|location=[[舊金山|舊金山]]|isbn=0872864766|edition=1st}}</ref>。最初的全球監控行為，為1946年3月5日簽定的[[英美協定|英美協定]]（此協定之參與國之後延伸至[[加拿大|加拿大]]、[[澳大利亞|澳大利亞]]與[[紐西蘭|紐西蘭]]等共五國，又稱為「[[五眼聯盟|五眼聯盟]]」），宗旨在於共享各項軍事與機密情報，以有效因應[[冷戰|冷戰]]時期變化的國際情勢。「五眼聯盟」與幾個「第三方」國家簽定了合作條款，最終在1971建立了代號為「[[梯隊系統|梯隊系統]]」的全球監控網路<ref name="auto">{{cite news|language=en|title=Q&A: What you need to know about Echelon|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/sci/tech/1357513.stm|publisher=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]]|date=2001-05-29|accessdate=2017-03-22|archive-date=2013-12-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131218051611/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/sci/tech/1357513.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Nabbali 2004 84–97">{{cite journal|language=en|last=Nabbali|first=Talitha|author2=Perry, Mark|title=Going for the throat|journal=Computer Law & Security Review|date=March 2004|volume=20|issue=2|pages=第84–97頁|doi=10.1016/S0267-3649(04)00018-4|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0267364904000184|quote=It wasn't until 1971 that the UKUSA allies began ECHELON|access-date=2017-03-22|archive-date=2016-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160204180330/http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0267364904000184|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

然而，由於[[愛德華·史諾登|愛德華·史諾登]]在2013年{{link-en|曝光了全球監聽項目|Global surveillance disclosures (2013–present)}}的國家秘密文檔，引發公眾對[[資訊時代|資訊時代]][[隱私權|隱私權]]的爭論，政府和主流媒體的存在也受到廣泛的質疑<ref>{{cite journal|language=en|last=Zevenbergen|first=Bendert|title=Adventures in digital surveillance|journal=European View|date=2013-12-03|volume=12|issue=2|pages=第223–233頁|doi=10.1007/s12290-013-0287-x|url=http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12290-013-0287-x|accessdate=2013-12-17|quote=Snowden used the press to inform the world that a global surveillance state may be being built. This led to the beginning of a global political debate on digital communications surveillance.|archive-date=2013-12-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217225008/http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12290-013-0287-x|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="RangerSteve1">{{cite web | language=en | url=http://www.techrepublic.com/article/the-undercover-war-on-your-internet-secrets-how-online-surveillance-cracked-our-trust-in-the-web/ | title=The undercover war on your internet secrets: How online surveillance cracked our trust in the web | last=Ranger | first=Steve | work= | publisher=TechRepublic | date=2015-03-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612190952/http://www.techrepublic.com/article/the-undercover-war-on-your-internet-secrets-how-online-surveillance-cracked-our-trust-in-the-web/ | archive-date=2016-06-12 | access-date=2016-06-12 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

